name: Egyptian Mythology
title: Sekhmet (Sakhmet) - Egyptian Mythology
epithets: Goddess of War, Healing, and Divine Vengeance
description: Sekhmet is the lioness-headed goddess of war, plague, and healing. The Eye ofRasent to punish rebellious humanity, she became drunk on bloodlust until tricked byRainto drinking beer dyed red. Consort ofPtah, mother of Nefertum. Both destroyer and healer - her priests were physicians who could cause or cure disease.
